CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 5, 1963, pg. 3, reads: "Freedom Singers - Shown singing at the United Negro Protest Committee's meeting, Sunday, at Bethesda Presbyterian Church, Homewood, are the members of the Children's Choir of North View Heights Presbyterian Church, where Rev. John Garvin is minster. Mrs. Emma Davis is choir director. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Man, possibly Judge Henry Smith speaking at podium to crowd, including Alma Speed Fox, James O. Dougan, and Helen Sharpe Dougan, in Bethesda Presbyterian Church, for United Negro Protest Committee meeting
